Two suspects aged 36 and 40 are expected to appear in the Mokopane Magistrate s Court on a charge of stock theft today (Friday). Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said the suspects were arrested during a joint operation by the Mokopane Stock Theft Unit and Crime Intelligence Unit yesterday (Thursday). Ten live goats and a vehicle used to transport the animals were confiscated. Investigations continue, Ngoepe said. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com Featured photo: Ten allegedly stolen goats were recovered during a Police operation in Mokopane yesterday (Thursday). (photo supplied) &nbsp;